 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uglorianafrostglitter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloriana Frostglitter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1493<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/28/02 1:51:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3442.topic&index=110>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also one question for the agnostics. Kind of a pissy question. Since you belive in no god. Of any type. Do you have a soul?<br>
<br>
Not a pleasent question to ask is it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As an atheist, the question isn't unpleasant, it's fairly innocuous and more a matter of intellectual debate than a fear of endless torment in the fiery pits of hell after death.  I'm not even sure what a &quot;soul&quot; is or if you know what a soul is either.<br>
<br>
I don't strive to be a good person because I am afraid of the consequences to my soul after death, I don't need a religion to cow me into good behavior.<br>
<br>
To quote Peter Pan: &quot;To die will be an awfully great adventure.&quot;<br>
<br>
As an atheist, I'm a bit jealous of those with faith, it must be an easier way to get through life.  I've heard there are no atheists on a deathbed and I've often thought of believing just to be on the safe side, who wants to suffer eternal damnation?  I wonder, if I die and there is a God and he punishes me for my disbelief on Earth by sending me to hell, will the horror of being in Hell be mitigated by my joy that there is a God?  <br>
<br>
