I must disagree with you on one thing though:  Having faith is not easier than not having it.  Believing in an absolute right and wrong and conforming ones behaviour to that yardstick is damn hard.  I believe it is easier to believe that there is no ultimate right or wrong set by some other power, and that there are not cosmic repercussions to my choices.<br>
