Personally, my pursuit of who God is began with a recognition that there is simply too much wonder in the world for it to all be an accident.  Science screams INTENT when I've studied it (former Nuclear Engineering student - changed my mind and went to Psych).  The duck-billed Platypus, sunsets, water (chemical formula stuff) and breasts, all prove that a loving Creator exists in the world.  [I am serious about all four, by the way, and not just comic relief.] <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxisix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xisix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/28/02 2:57:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3442.topic&index=114>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> /cheer <br>
