Yes, but the absolute right and wrong is handed to you, you don't have to do a lot of thinking about the hows and whys of your behavior.  You do x or don't do y because that's what the Bible tells you.<br>
<br>
You rarely have to think, &quot;what should I do in this situation?&quot; Chances are, some scripture had already laid out the path for you, you must simply adhere.<br>
<br>
That fact that I don't worry about the cosmic repercussions for my actions means I am also denied the prospect of cosmic rewards for my actions.<br>
<br>
Surely it's a lot simpler to think, &quot;after I die, I'm going to heaven!&quot; Then to think, &quot;I wonder what happens when you die?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uathao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>athao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/28/02 3:20:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3442.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> -</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The duck-billed Platypus, sunsets, water (chemical formula stuff) and breasts, all prove that a loving Creator exists in the world.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
